{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated reply references specific points from the incoming email rather than producing a generic response.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The failure boundary is the model’s semantic behavior: a mocked or deterministic stub can appear correct while a real LLM still returns vague/generic text. Correctness depends on real model output quality and can vary run to run.","test_description":"Run generation with a real LLM on a corpus of real/representative threads containing concrete details (dates, asks, constraints). Assert the draft includes thread-specific references (entity/intent overlap or rubric-based grader) and fails when outputs are generic. Execute multiple trials per thread to capture nondeterministic misses.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The factual consistency check flags claims in the draft that contradict entries in the knowledge base.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a cross-module handoff/state-wiring risk (draft claim extraction -> KB retrieval/query -> contradiction rule/decision). Pure unit mocks can miss real schema/query/index mismatches that cause missed flags.","test_description":"Use real checker wiring with a local KB fixture and seeded contradictory/non-contradictory drafts. Verify contradictions are flagged and aligned claims are not. Do not mock repository/query boundaries; exercise actual parsing, retrieval, and rule evaluation path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When the knowledge base has no relevant entries, the draft includes a disclaimer rather than fabricating facts.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Even with correct empty-retrieval wiring, real failure is often hallucination behavior from the model under uncertainty. Mocked generation can hide this by always returning compliant text.","test_description":"Run end-to-end draft generation with real LLM and intentionally irrelevant/empty KB retrieval results. Assert the output contains the required disclaimer and does not introduce unsupported factual claims; repeat across multiple runs/prompts to catch stochastic fabrication.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The approval workflow blocks sending until the user explicitly approves — no draft is sent automatically.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is gating/state propagation across components (UI/approval state -> send service). A unit test of one function can miss real wiring bugs that trigger send before approval.","test_description":"Wire real approval-state store and send dispatcher with a test transport. Simulate draft creation without approval and verify no send event/API call occurs; then approve explicitly and verify exactly one send occurs. Cover race/retry path to ensure gating is enforced.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — read thread, generate draft, check facts, present for approval — works end-to-end for a real email thread.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is explicitly a full agent pipeline across multiple stages, including at least one real agentic step (generation) and sequential orchestration. Lower-level tests won’t catch cross-stage degradation and policy drift in the complete flow.","test_description":"Execute the full pipeline on real email-thread input (or production-like mailbox fixture), real LLM draft generation, real fact-check stage, and real approval gate. Assert stage outputs and transitions: thread parsed, draft generated, contradictions/disclaimer behavior applied, approval required before send. Validate final send only after approval.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.13,"Workflow":0.7}}]}
